Text: Without limiting subclause 1.3, the Australian Privacy Principle privacy policy of the Australian Privacy Principle entity must contain the following information:

a) the kinds of personal information that the entity collects and holds;
b) how the entity collects and holds personal information;
c) the purposes for which the entity collects, holds, uses and discloses personal information;
d) how an individual may access personal information about the individual that is held by the entity and seek the correction of such information;
